        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 3:40PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 340 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Fresno. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Western Pearland, southeastern Missouri City, Manvel, Fresno, Arcola,
Iowa Colony, Fort Bend Houston, eastern Sienna, and Juliff.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
